               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>مراة البيان</p>
                     <p>The Mirʼāt al-bayān (Mirror of the Bayán), an autograph by Ṣubḥ-i-Ezel
                        containing commentary on 137 divine "Names," arranged similarly to (but in a
                        different order and not grouped in Váḥids of 19, unlike) the "Commentary on
                        the Names" described at <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_582">F. 16 (BBF.
                           9)</ref> and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_583">F. 17 (BBF.
                           10)</ref>. Browne states the title aptly describes the work, taking
                        "Bayán" in the sense denoting these "Books of Names." It was copied for me
                        in 1891 and received in instalments during this and the following year. It
                        comprises 678 ff. of 20'5x13'5 c. and 14 ll.</p>
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_45-item1">
                     <author key="person_266910202" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/266910202/"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="aut scr"
                           change="#role-assignment">Ṣubḥ-i Azal, d. 1912</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar" role="aut scr" change="#role-assignment">صبح
                           ازل</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2632">Mirʼāt al-bayān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_2632">مرآة البيان</title>
                     <note>Browne lists all 137 Names contained in the work; only a sample is given
                        here. Groups of Names are given in the original as bracketed subsets of 20
                        approx. each.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">لا اله الا الله مرآت البیان
                        لباب فی معرفة اسم الالوهیة و له اربع نقاط الاول فی الاول بسم الله الاله
                        الاله...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">... و الیه من الراجعین ذلک
                        الفضل من عنده و العود من لدنه... (ff. 674a-675a)</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/99"
                              >p.73</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBF. 11</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and
                           Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the
                           Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892):
                           637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"></bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
